<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The people who helped bring down <PERSON> Ivan </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Boesky </PERSON> are moving up _ two floors _ and over about seven blocks. The <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> regional office of the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> will be trading its longtime base at 26 Federal Plaza in lower <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> for new quarters near the World Trade Center later this month. After more than 20 years at the aging, 42-story government office building that also houses the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Immigration </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Naturalization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> and some 80 other federal agencies near the city's courts and municipal buildings, the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> local staff is moving into private office space closer to the financial district it regulates. The agency will exchange the slighty shabby federal building with its beige walls and balky elevators for two entire floors atop 75 Park Place, a sleek, glass and metal, 13-story office building that opened less than two years ago. The <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> office, biggest of the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION>'s nine regional offices, will be expanding its office space from 34,000 square feet to 40,000 square feet, according to <PERSON> Renee </PERSON> <PERSON> Miscione </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for the <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>, which administers federal office buildings. Other tenants in the new location include the publisher R.R. <ORGANIZATION> Donnelly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Sons and the legal department of the city's housing authority. While <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> Regional Administrator <PERSON> Lawrence </PERSON> <PERSON> Iason </PERSON> and his staff of about 200 are happy about the move, they also do n't have much choice. The 850 staffers of the federal <ORGANIZATION> Environmental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Protection </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, who already occupy parts of 12 floors at 26 Federal Plaza, need more space and the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION>'s offices fit the bill. `` But it's not like -LRB- the move -RRB- is n't beneficial,'' <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Heyl </PERSON>, regional counsel for the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, said during a recent interview as she tried to find room for storing 100 office chairs that arrived three weeks early. The public reference room, where company filings and other <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> documents are made available, will be expanded slightly, said <PERSON> Iason </PERSON>.
